{
  "texts": [
    "Accordingly, the pupil is known to be the darkest element within the eye region (Drakopoulos et al. 2021).",
    "Captured images can be slightly enhanced for later detection through the suppression of reflections, defined as image regions with abrupt intensity peaks.",
    "To achieve this, bright regions are averaged with their neighbors.",
    "Due to their low contrast, an histogram equalization such as Contrast Limited Adaptive Histogram Equalization (CLAHE) can also be applied (Drakopoulos et al. 2020 (Drakopoulos et al., 2021)).",
    "Concerning the procedure core, Dong et al. (2020) proposed to enhance the image contrast, apply a Haar-cascade eye detector (implemented in OpenCV) and threshold the image to output a binary image."
  ]
}